    public class CBuildFromCollection

    • Constructor Detail

      • CBuildFromCollection

        public CBuildFromCollection(String name,
                    Collection<?> source,
                    Class<?> stopClass,
                    String primaryKeyPropNames)
        Builds a data cache from the given Collection. Introspection is used to determine the bean properties (i.e.: getter methods) that are exposed, and each one becomes a column in the data cache.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the data cache to create.
        source - the Java collection to convert.
        stopClass - Columns are created for all getter methods that are defined by stopClass's subclasses. stopClass's getter methods and superclass getter methods are not converted to columns in the dataframe.
        primaryKeyPropNames - property names of the primary key(s), separated by commas, eg: "firstname,lastname" (NB: do not include a space after the comma), or null if no primary key.

    • Method Detail

      • setReportBoxedType

        public CBuildFromCollection setReportBoxedType(boolean reportBoxedPrimitive)
        Determine whether primitive bean properties return a primitive type or a boxed type. By default a boxed type is reported. This doesn't affect the storing of the value, it only means the CMetaData for the created container will report a boxed type, eg: java.lang.Integer instead of int.
        Parameters:
        reportBoxedPrimitive - whether bean properties returning a primitive type should report these as a boxed type.
        Returns:
        this. Can be chained.
